}}'''''VODAC: The Alpine Encounter''''' is a 1983 [[adventure game]] for the [[Apple II]] published by [[Ibid-inc]].<ref name=incider/>

==Gameplay==
''VODAC: The Alpine Encounter'' is an espionage game in which the player must stop an evil plot at an alpine ski resort.<ref name="SG"/> While primarily an adventure, it includes a skiing action game.<ref name=incider/>

==Reception==
James A. McPherson reviewed the program for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "An intermediate level game, The Alpine Encounter has detailed graphics similar to other current graphic adventure games."<ref name="CGW16">{{cite magazine |last=McPherson |first=James A. |title=Micro-Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=June 1984 |volume=1 |issue=16 |pages=34}}</ref>

Terry Rooker reviewed ''VODAC: The Alpine Encounter'' in ''[[Space Gamer]]'' No. 73.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Rooker |first=Terry |date=Mar–Apr 1985 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=73|pages=39–40}}</ref> Rooker commented that "For people who like espionage adventures, ''VODAC'' can be fun and exciting.  First you have to figure out the correct commands to be used; then you have to solve the mystery and save the world. If you are willing to accept this dual challenge, ''VODAC: The Alpine Encounter'' is the game for you."<ref name="SG"/>

